01:13:28.850 --> 01:13:31.540
So everything we've been hearing
about with the neurobiology--

01:13:31.540 --> 01:13:34.110
and we're still living in
this part, in this bucket here

01:13:34.110 --> 01:13:36.020
temporarily-- has
been built around

01:13:36.020 --> 01:13:37.930
heterosexual relationships.

01:13:37.930 --> 01:13:40.130
What's known about
the neurobiology

01:13:40.130 --> 01:13:42.500
of sexual orientation?

01:13:42.500 --> 01:13:47.790
What has been found is most
strikingly one landmark study,

01:13:47.790 --> 01:13:50.920
one that got on the
cover of Time magazine,

01:13:50.920 --> 01:13:54.300
one that had a gigantic,
gigantic impact,

01:13:54.300 --> 01:13:57.640
which was looking back at
that hypothalamic nucleus,

01:13:57.640 --> 01:14:01.280
that INAH, I-N-A-H. Yes.

01:14:01.280 --> 01:14:03.850
Where what we saw
before was very reliably

01:14:03.850 --> 01:14:07.690
on the average, men, their
size of it is about twice

01:14:07.690 --> 01:14:09.360
the size as in women.

01:14:09.360 --> 01:14:12.120
And in other species,
males about twice

01:14:12.120 --> 01:14:14.040
the size as in females.

01:14:14.040 --> 01:14:16.610
And a study was
done in the late 80s

01:14:16.610 --> 01:14:19.470
by a neuroanatomist
names Simon LeVay.

01:14:19.470 --> 01:14:21.800
LeVay is one of the all-time
great neuroanatomists.

01:14:21.800 --> 01:14:24.250
He was trained by
Hubel and Wiesel,

01:14:24.250 --> 01:14:26.650
was a professor at
Harvard Med School

01:14:26.650 --> 01:14:29.110
for a while before moving
to the Salk Institute.

01:14:29.110 --> 01:14:31.880
And what he did was
look post-mortem

01:14:31.880 --> 01:14:34.630
at the brains of a bunch of
individuals where he knew

01:14:34.630 --> 01:14:36.900
the sexual orientation, men.

01:14:36.900 --> 01:14:41.180
And what he showed was gay
men, on the average, had

01:14:41.180 --> 01:14:45.270
this nucleus on the
average was half the size

01:14:45.270 --> 01:14:48.060
that you saw in
heterosexual men.

01:14:48.060 --> 01:14:50.940
On the average, it was
about the same size

01:14:50.940 --> 01:14:53.800
as you saw in
heterosexual women.

01:14:53.800 --> 01:14:56.330
Amazing landmark study.

01:14:56.330 --> 01:14:59.670
Everybody learned about
the homosexual brain

01:14:59.670 --> 01:15:00.800
from this study.

01:15:00.800 --> 01:15:03.850
Hugely widely reported.

01:15:03.850 --> 01:15:06.680
And this is kind of interesting.

01:15:06.680 --> 01:15:07.180
OK.

01:15:07.180 --> 01:15:08.360
What's interesting about it?

01:15:08.360 --> 01:15:12.690
First off, the question you need
to ask is how much variability?

01:15:12.690 --> 01:15:13.510
Fair amount.

01:15:13.510 --> 01:15:15.890
It wasn't all that
reliable of a difference.

01:15:15.890 --> 01:15:19.920
On the average, it was
about a half the size.

01:15:19.920 --> 01:15:21.295
Next thing you
would want to know

01:15:21.295 --> 01:15:24.480
is, has anybody
replicated it since then?

01:15:24.480 --> 01:15:25.830
Yes.

01:15:25.830 --> 01:15:27.340
Next thing you
would want to know

01:15:27.340 --> 01:15:30.180
