get the brains from?

01:15:30.180 --> 01:15:32.310
And these were
predominantly from gay men

01:15:32.310 --> 01:15:33.940
who had died of AIDS.

01:15:33.940 --> 01:15:35.570
Is that a confound?

01:15:35.570 --> 01:15:39.430
Is that going to perhaps
atrophy this part of the brain?

01:15:39.430 --> 01:15:40.540
Nobody knows.

01:15:40.540 --> 01:15:43.610
So that remains as a
caveat in that study.

01:15:43.610 --> 01:15:46.980
What was striking
though was everybody

01:15:46.980 --> 01:15:48.740
learned about this finding.

01:15:48.740 --> 01:15:50.370
This became famous.

01:15:50.370 --> 01:15:52.880
LeVay became extremely
famous for this.

01:15:52.880 --> 01:15:54.380
And what was also
very interesting

01:15:54.380 --> 01:15:57.950
about it was the political
context of this finding.

01:15:57.950 --> 01:16:00.750
A few years before
that, another group

01:16:00.750 --> 01:16:04.420
had reported another
difference in the hypothalamus

01:16:04.420 --> 01:16:06.520
based on sexual orientation.

01:16:06.520 --> 01:16:12.640
And this was-- there it is.

01:16:12.640 --> 01:16:15.100
And what you found was in
this part of the brain,

01:16:15.100 --> 01:16:20.210
on the average, it would tend
be bigger in women than in men.

01:16:20.210 --> 01:16:23.900
And what these guys
reported was in gay men,

01:16:23.900 --> 01:16:28.230
it tended to be bigger
than in straight men.

01:16:28.230 --> 01:16:30.010
What was puzzling
about the study

01:16:30.010 --> 01:16:32.730
was this was a part of
a hypothalamus having

01:16:32.730 --> 01:16:35.840
to do with regulation
of your kidneys.

01:16:35.840 --> 01:16:38.950
And it was totally ignored
and completely bizarre,

01:16:38.950 --> 01:16:40.540
except there was
one thing that was

01:16:40.540 --> 01:16:42.730
done with it, which
was this was viewed

01:16:42.730 --> 01:16:46.670
as a totally offensive
study in the gay community.

01:16:46.670 --> 01:16:49.160
This was viewed as an
attempt by scientists

01:16:49.160 --> 01:16:53.640
to pathologize sexual
orientation, to say, you see,

01:16:53.640 --> 01:16:58.130
we found something wrong in
the brains of homosexual men.

01:16:58.130 --> 01:17:01.410
This part of the brain is
bigger than it should be.

01:17:01.410 --> 01:17:03.400
It's bigger than
it's supposed to be.

01:17:03.400 --> 01:17:06.190
There's probably two
reasons why that occurred.

01:17:06.190 --> 01:17:09.730
The first one was that
the scientists who did it

01:17:09.730 --> 01:17:11.430
were straight.

01:17:11.430 --> 01:17:14.530
And the second reason being
that they were a Dutch group.

01:17:14.530 --> 01:17:17.260
And I am willing to
bet unconsciously there

01:17:17.260 --> 01:17:22.350
was something central European
Nazi echoes of Germanic

01:17:22.350 --> 01:17:25.490
sounding authors producing
this finding, which there

01:17:25.490 --> 01:17:28.750
is no shortage of history in
the gay community for being

01:17:28.750 --> 01:17:31.650
skittish about Nazi
notions of what normality

01:17:31.650 --> 01:17:34.350
is in human behavior
and human brains.

01:17:34.350 --> 01:17:38.650
This finding got widely
condemned in the gay community.

01:17:38.650 --> 01:17:43.820
Out came LeVay with his
finding, and he became the most

01:17:43.820 --> 01:17:48.600
beloved neuroanatomist ever in
the history of gay communities.

01:17:48.600 --> 01:17:51.310
One probably important
feature reason for it

01:17:51.310 --> 01:17:54.860
is that LeVay was
gay, very openly so.

01:17:54.860 --> 01:17:58.830
Another reason was the part of
the brain he found made sense.

01:17:58.830 --> 01:18:02.370
It had something to do with
sexual behavior as opposed

01:18:02.370 --> 01:18:04.710
to the totally puzzling thing.

01:18:04.710 --> 01:18:06.440
So what was this about?

01:18:06.440 --> 01:18:09.790
Very interestingly, the
explanation almost certainly

01:18:09.790 --> 01:18:12.780
is that this was the
part of the hypothalamus

01:18:12.780 --> 01:18:15.800
next door to the area
that LeVay studied.

01:18:15.800 --> 01:18:19.950
And if this part were
smaller in gay men

01:18:19.950 --> 01:18:23.380
simply because of just
physical constraints stuff,

01:18:23.380 --> 01:18:25.710
this part could get
bigger in gay men.

01:18:25.710 --> 01:18:27.890
Because this one was
taking up less area.

01:18:27.890 --> 01:18:29.800
That's probably
what was going on.

01:18:29.800 --> 01:18:33.820
What's really fascinating
though is the political context

01:18:33.820 --> 01:18:35.760
that this research was done in.

01:18:35.760 --> 01:18:38.970
And this was that first group,
the senior author of it,

01:18:38.970 --> 01:18:40.850
a man named Dick Schwab.

01:18:40.850 --> 01:18:44.730
And he got death threats
because of that study reporting,

01:18:44.730 --> 01:18:48.500
ooh, here is-- easily
interpreted as-- something

01:18:48.500 --> 01:18:51.380
wrong in the brains of gay man.

01:18:51.380 --> 01:18:55.120
And Simon LeVay became
the hero in the community.

01:18:55.120 --> 01:18:57.820
This was utterly embraced
by the community.

01:18:57.820 --> 01:19:00.990
Because in large part,
how it was interpreted as,

01:19:00.990 --> 01:19:02.730
this is biology.

01:19:02.730 --> 01:19:04.160
This isn't choice.

01:19:04.160 --> 01:19:05.510
This is biology.

01:19:05.510 --> 01:19:06.660
Look at this.

01:19:06.660 --> 01:19:09.250
This is ridiculous,
us saying, oh my god.

01:19:09.250 --> 01:19:11.440
If we have gay teachers
in the classroom,

01:19:11.440 --> 01:19:14.880
we will turn the Boy Scouts
of America into a gay men.

01:19:14.880 --> 01:19:18.050
Oh my god, if we have blue-eyed
teachers in the classroom--

01:19:18.050 --> 01:19:22.380
the usual argument that this is
absolute gibberish to demonize

01:19:22.380 --> 01:19:24.290
sexual orientation as a choice.

01:19:24.290 --> 01:19:24.910
Look at this.

01:19:24.910 --> 01:19:26.960
There's a neurobiology of it.

01:19:26.960 --> 01:19:31.020
And this was sufficiently that
I've seen people in the Castro

01:19:31.020 --> 01:19:33.550
District in San Francisco--
this has disappeared somewhat,

01:19:33.550 --> 01:19:36.290
showing the half life of
neuroanatomical knowledge.

01:19:36.290 --> 01:19:38.959
But during that time, people
in the Castro District up

01:19:38.959 --> 01:19:41.000
in the city there, which
is a very gay community,

01:19:41.000 --> 01:19:44.400
I have seen people with
t-shirts saying-- the other term

01:19:44.400 --> 01:19:47.930
people never really wanted
to embrace this INAH,

01:19:47.930 --> 01:19:51.050
so its nickname was the
sexually dimorphic nucleus

01:19:51.050 --> 01:19:52.450
of the hypothalamus.

01:19:52.450 --> 01:19:54.430
And I have seen people
with t-shirts saying,

01:19:54.430 --> 01:19:58.025
the only small thing about me is
my sexually dimorphic nucleus.

01:20:00.530 --> 01:20:02.950
They were actually
selling t-shirts

01:20:02.950 --> 01:20:06.690
that would say this during
gay pride parades around 1990

01:20:06.690 --> 01:20:07.410
or so.

01:20:07.410 --> 01:20:10.000
Isn't it great when
people learn neuroanatomy

01:20:10.000 --> 01:20:12.140
out in the general public there?

01:20:12.140 --> 01:20:12.840
OK.

01:20:12.840 --> 01:20:15.950
So an interesting
brain difference

01:20:15.950 --> 01:20:18.880
confounded by people
who died of AIDS.

01:20:18.880 --> 01:20:20.960
It's still not clear
what that means

01:20:20.960 --> 01:20:23.850
in terms of possibly
negating the finding at least

01:20:23.850 --> 01:20:25.440
independently replicated.

01:20:25.440 --> 01:20:27.600
Fascinating piece
of not science,

01:20:27.600 --> 01:20:30.320
but the political
context of science.

01:20:30.320 --> 01:20:34.360
This politically incorrect
to an extreme, this very,

01:20:34.360 --> 01:20:36.000
very widely embraced.

01:20:36.000 --> 01:20:38.920
One interesting thing is
that paper by LeVay of

01:20:38.920 --> 01:20:40.770
was published in
the journal Science.

01:20:40.770 --> 01:20:44.140
Again, constantly mentioned as
probably the most influential

01:20:44.140 --> 01:20:46.110
science journal in this country.

01:20:46.110 --> 01:20:49.030
And it was published--
what year was it? '88.

01:20:49.030 --> 01:20:51.390
'88, '92, '90?

01:20:51.390 --> 01:20:51.890
OK.

01:20:51.890 --> 01:20:53.100
I'm getting the year wrong.

01:20:53.100 --> 01:20:57.000
But it was just before the
Clinton election against Bush

01:20:57.000 --> 01:21:00.180
where one of the big issues
was gays in the military.

01:21:00.180 --> 01:21:02.550
That was the first thing
that Clinton turned to

01:21:02.550 --> 01:21:03.820
after he was elected.

01:21:03.820 --> 01:21:06.450
I happen to know the man
who is the editor of Science

01:21:06.450 --> 01:21:07.330
at the time.

01:21:07.330 --> 01:21:08.880
And they timed the publication.

01:21:08.880 --> 01:21:11.570
That paper came out in
late October of that year.

01:21:11.570 --> 01:21:14.270
And they held it for
that time because they

01:21:14.270 --> 01:21:17.830
knew that this was going to be
an issue in the election, which

01:21:17.830 --> 01:21:21.480
was kind of cool that they did
that, although some people may

01:21:21.480 --> 01:21:22.410
disagree.

01:21:22.410 --> 01:21:22.910
OK.

01:21:22.910 --> 01:21:24.040
But we hurtle on.

01:21:24.040 --> 01:21:27.560
So what other biological,
neurobiological differences,

01:21:27.560 --> 01:21:29.780
as a function of
sexual orientation?

01:21:29.780 --> 01:21:32.980
Another one that comes through
over and over and over again,

01:21:32.980 --> 01:21:35.280
which-- what do
you make of this--

01:21:35.280 --> 01:21:38.950
is apparently there is a
reliable gender difference

01:21:38.950 --> 01:21:41.110
in the length of
the second finger

01:21:41.110 --> 01:21:44.150
versus the fourth finger,
the ratio of the two.

01:21:44.150 --> 01:21:47.020
And just to show how bi--
whoa, did a lot of hands

01:21:47.020 --> 01:21:49.300
just go up in this auditorium.

01:21:49.300 --> 01:21:51.690
And just to show how
biologically compelling

01:21:51.690 --> 01:21:54.190
the explanation is for
it, I don't actually

01:21:54.190 --> 01:21:58.250
remember which like-- who's
got the greater four to two

01:21:58.250 --> 01:22:00.620
ratio, which sex, or whatever.

01:22:00.620 --> 01:22:02.900
But it is a very--
now people are

01:22:02.900 --> 01:22:04.840
checking each other's hands.

01:22:04.840 --> 01:22:05.450
OK.

01:22:05.450 --> 01:22:10.200
The first wave of-- and now
all this chimp hand inspection

01:22:10.200 --> 01:22:11.660
stuff happening in here.

01:22:11.660 --> 01:22:15.200
And what has been shown
quite reliably since then is,

01:22:15.200 --> 01:22:18.550
on the average, gay men tend
to have the finger length

01:22:18.550 --> 01:22:22.080
ratio of straight women
rather than of straight men.

01:22:22.080 --> 01:22:23.860
A small effect there.

01:22:23.860 --> 01:22:26.920
Another even more
bizarre finding,

01:22:26.920 --> 01:22:31.720
which is there is something
called the autoacoustic reflex.

01:22:31.720 --> 01:22:35.300
And what that is is if you sit
there and plug your ears up

01:22:35.300 --> 01:22:37.980
with your fingers, you will
hear a noise that is just

01:22:37.980 --> 01:22:40.560
coming from the intrinsic
vibration of something

01:22:40.560 --> 01:22:42.220
right there in your
ears, and that's

01:22:42.220 --> 01:22:45.240
the autoacoustic reflex
generating some low Hertz

01:22:45.240 --> 01:22:46.440
sound in there.

01:22:46.440 --> 01:22:50.950
And the rate of the oscillation
differs by sex in humans,

01:22:50.950 --> 01:22:53.240
which no doubt
explains everything

01:22:53.240 --> 01:22:56.990
about the tragic
wars of the sexes

01:22:56.990 --> 01:22:59.380
and why people just don't
understand each other

01:22:59.380 --> 01:23:02.490
by gender because of their ears
vibrating at different speeds.

01:23:02.490 --> 01:23:04.260
But what these studies
have also shown

01:23:04.260 --> 01:23:07.700
was gay men having the
autoacoustic reflexive

01:23:07.700 --> 01:23:10.850
vibratory speed more
typical of straight women

01:23:10.850 --> 01:23:11.710
than straight men.

01:23:11.710 --> 01:23:13.710
Again, a very small effect.

01:23:13.710 --> 01:23:15.490
What are all of these about?

01:23:15.490 --> 01:23:17.480
The assumptions
are it's got to do

01:23:17.480 --> 01:23:20.980
with something with prenatal
hormone environment.

01:23:20.980 --> 01:23:21.750
Stay tuned.

01:23:21.750 --> 01:23:24.070
We will be coming back to this.

01:23:24.070 --> 01:23:26.120
Now somewhere in
there you may ask, OK,

01:23:26.120 --> 01:23:29.490
well what about the neurobiology
of sexual orientation in women?

01:23:29.490 --> 01:23:31.660
Vastly smaller literature.

01:23:31.660 --> 01:23:33.460
Far, far less studied.

01:23:33.460 --> 01:23:36.780
What has been shown so far
are only two endpoints.

01:23:36.780 --> 01:23:40.820
One is the same deal with the
fourth to second finger ratio.

01:23:40.820 --> 01:23:44.980
On the average, gay women
have the ratio more typical

01:23:44.980 --> 01:23:46.615
of straight men
than straight women.

01:23:46.615 --> 01:23:47.990
The other thing
that's been shown

01:23:47.990 --> 01:23:52.050
is the same autoacoustic
reflex thingy going on there.

01:23:52.050 --> 01:23:54.890
Final realm of
neurobiology, rather than

01:23:54.890 --> 01:23:57.950
issues of gay versus
straight, what

01:23:57.950 --> 01:24:01.000
is the neurobiology
of transsexuality?

01:24:01.000 --> 01:24:04.020
And that used to be
considered to be purely

01:24:04.020 --> 01:24:06.660
a domain of psychopathology.

01:24:06.660 --> 01:24:10.660
If being gay used to be
a certifiable psychiatric

01:24:10.660 --> 01:24:14.450
disorder-- up until the early
1970s, the American Psychiatric

01:24:14.450 --> 01:24:17.200
Association in their textbook,
the Diagnostic Statistical

01:24:17.200 --> 01:24:21.090
Manual, you could be
psychiatrically certified

01:24:21.090 --> 01:24:21.620
as ill.

01:24:21.620 --> 01:24:25.710
A psychiatric disorder was
being homosexual or lesbian.

01:24:25.710 --> 01:24:28.370
And then in what had to
have been one of the more

01:24:28.370 --> 01:24:31.310
all-time blow out
committee meetings ever,

01:24:31.310 --> 01:24:33.510
they decided that,
no, actually it's

01:24:33.510 --> 01:24:34.780
not a psychiatric disorder.

01:24:34.780 --> 01:24:37.100
And overnight, about
40 million Americans

01:24:37.100 --> 01:24:39.330
were cured of a
psychiatric disease.

01:24:39.330 --> 01:24:43.410
The notion of transsexuality
as a psychiatric disorder

01:24:43.410 --> 01:24:46.320
has had much, much
longer shelf life.

01:24:46.320 --> 01:24:49.020
What's the neurobiology of that?

01:24:49.020 --> 01:24:52.350
To date, there have been
a handful of studies,

01:24:52.350 --> 01:24:55.490
and they show essentially
the same thing-- really,

01:24:55.490 --> 01:24:56.900
really interesting.

01:24:56.900 --> 01:24:59.310
Another region of
the brain that shows

01:24:59.310 --> 01:25:01.340
a sex difference in
its average size--

01:25:01.340 --> 01:25:03.580
don't even worry about
the name of this.

01:25:03.580 --> 01:25:06.790
It's called the bed nucleus
of the stria terminalis.

01:25:06.790 --> 01:25:09.950
It's where the amygdala
begins to send its projection

01:25:09.950 --> 01:25:11.370
into the hypothalamus.

01:25:11.370 --> 01:25:13.820
Another one to those
gender differences.

01:25:13.820 --> 01:25:16.320
There is one type
of neuron in there

01:25:16.320 --> 01:25:20.190
with a certain type of
neurotransmitter, where very,

01:25:20.190 --> 01:25:23.690
very reliably it is about
twice the size in males

01:25:23.690 --> 01:25:24.790
than in females.

01:25:24.790 --> 01:25:26.870
Sufficiently so that
even in human brains,

01:25:26.870 --> 01:25:29.800
you could pretty confidently
determine the sex of somebody

01:25:29.800 --> 01:25:31.550
by seeing the number
of these neurons.

01:25:31.550 --> 01:25:33.030
You'll see, I'm not
even saying the name

01:25:33.030 --> 01:25:34.030
of the neurotransmitter.

01:25:34.030 --> 01:25:34.710
It's irrelevant.

01:25:34.710 --> 01:25:37.050
It's just another one
of those differences,

01:25:37.050 --> 01:25:40.850
a dimorphism in a region of
the brain, a really, really

01:25:40.850 --> 01:25:42.490
reliable one.

01:25:42.490 --> 01:25:47.140
And this was a study done by
some superb neuroanatomists

01:25:47.140 --> 01:25:49.980
looking at transsexuals.

01:25:49.980 --> 01:25:52.680
And what they showed
was very interesting,

01:25:52.680 --> 01:25:57.900
which was very, very reliably
and a very powerful effect.

01:25:57.900 --> 01:26:00.540
What you would see
in their large sample

01:26:00.540 --> 01:26:03.500
size of transsexuals
brains post-mortem

01:26:03.500 --> 01:26:07.760
was people would have this
part of the brain, the size not

01:26:07.760 --> 01:26:12.150
of their sex that they were
born with, but rather of the sex

01:26:12.150 --> 01:26:16.280
they insisted they
always actually were.

01:26:16.280 --> 01:26:17.520
Wow.

01:26:17.520 --> 01:26:19.921
Immediate questions
one must ask.

01:26:19.921 --> 01:26:20.420
OK.

01:26:20.420 --> 01:26:22.330
Well, maybe this
is due to the fact

01:26:22.330 --> 01:26:26.450
that when people change
gender, transsexual procedures,

01:26:26.450 --> 01:26:29.610
there's a whole lot
of hormones involved.

01:26:29.610 --> 01:26:32.510
And maybe that's doing something
to this part of the brain.

01:26:32.510 --> 01:26:35.130
Critical control
that they had was

01:26:35.130 --> 01:26:37.250
this was looking
both at transsexuals

01:26:37.250 --> 01:26:41.210
who had made gender changes and
those who went to their death

01:26:41.210 --> 01:26:44.130
bed saying this is
not the sex that I am,

01:26:44.130 --> 01:26:47.340
I got the wrong body, but
never made the change.

01:26:47.340 --> 01:26:49.270
It wasn't a function
of having actually

01:26:49.270 --> 01:26:52.730
gone through the transition
and the endocrine manipulations

01:26:52.730 --> 01:26:53.470
with it.

01:26:53.470 --> 01:26:56.230
Another control
they had, which was

01:26:56.230 --> 01:26:59.020
looking at men who would get
a certain type of testicular

01:26:59.020 --> 01:27:00.820
cancer where they
would have to be

01:27:00.820 --> 01:27:03.252
treated with certain
feminizing hormones.

01:27:03.252 --> 01:27:05.460
In other words, very similar
to some of the endocrine

01:27:05.460 --> 01:27:08.970
treatments of male-to-female
transgendered individuals.

01:27:08.970 --> 01:27:12.120
And post-mortem, you didn't
see the changes there.

01:27:12.120 --> 01:27:14.350
It has nothing to do
with the hormones.

01:27:14.350 --> 01:27:18.650
It had to do with the person
insisting from day one

01:27:18.650 --> 01:27:20.880
that they got the wrong body.

01:27:20.880 --> 01:27:23.930
And this was a landmark
study, fabulously

01:27:23.930 --> 01:27:26.730
well done and controlled,
and replicated once

01:27:26.730 --> 01:27:30.000
since then showing that
what transsexualism used

01:27:30.000 --> 01:27:32.180
to be thought of
is that people who

01:27:32.180 --> 01:27:35.380
think that they're a different
gender than they actually are.

01:27:35.380 --> 01:27:38.750
What this study suggests is
what transsexualism is about

01:27:38.750 --> 01:27:42.300
is people who got the
wrong gendered body.

01:27:42.300 --> 01:27:47.800
And these are people who are
chromosomally of one sex.

01:27:47.800 --> 01:27:50.110
In terms of their gonads,
they're of that sex.

01:27:50.110 --> 01:27:52.400
In terms of their hormones,
they're of that sex.

01:27:52.400 --> 01:27:55.310
In terms of their genitalia
and their secondary sexual

01:27:55.310 --> 01:27:57.650
characteristics,
they are of that sex.

01:27:57.650 --> 01:28:01.100
But they're insisting,
that's not who I really am.

01:28:01.100 --> 01:28:04.220
This part of the brain
agrees with them.

01:28:04.220 --> 01:28:06.560
Also very interestingly
that study

01:28:06.560 --> 01:28:10.360
was done by the same Dutch
scientists who did this one.

01:28:10.360 --> 01:28:13.790
